wikipedia_page.main: George Henry Camsell (27 November 1902 – 7 March 1966) was an English footballer who scored a club record 325 league goals in 419 games for Middlesbrough, and 18 goals in 9 appearances for England. His 59 goals in one season (1926–27) for Middlesbrough was a Football League record at the time, and has only been bettered once within the English game by Dixie Dean of Everton in 1927–28. His 9 hat-tricks that season remain a Football League record. He also holds the  highest goals-to-games ratio for England of anyone who has played more than a single international.
